name: Converse Chuck Taylor All-Star Pokemon Pikachu (TD)
Converse Chuck Taylor All-Star Pokemon Poke Ball
story: The Pokemon x Converse Chuck Taylor All Star High ‘Poke Ball’ celebrates 25 years of the iconic gaming franchise. An all-over Pokemon print is applied to the white canvas upper, lined in crimson textile and accented with a molded Poke Ball patch on the lateral ankle. Standard Chuck details remain intact, including a rubber toe cap, a circular All Star patch, and winged stitching atop the tongue. The high-top is mounted on a white rubber midsole with black pinstripe detailing and a custom Poke Ball license plate.

Converse Chuck Taylor All-Star Pokemon Jigglypuff (TD)
Nike Zoom Alpha Fly Next Nature Flat Pewter
story: The Nike Zoom Alphafly Next Nature ‘Rawdacious’ showcases pastel accents on a performance runner made with at least 50% recycled content by weight. The breathable textile upper, rendered in Flat Pewter with soft pink detailing on the tongue and collar, features layers of processed TPU that’s formed with an innovative 3D printing technology dubbed Nike Flyprint. Lightweight cushioning arrives via the combination of a carbon fiber spring plate and ZoomX foam midsole, fitted with two visible Zoom Air units under the forefoot.

name: Jordan 7 Retro Citrus (2022)
story: The 2022 edition of the Air Jordan 7 Retro ‘Citrus’ revives a non-OG colorway that was initially released in 2006. Like the original, the upper is constructed from black nubuck with a Huarache-like inner sleeve and contrast orange stitching throughout. The Citrus hue is repeated on the angular ‘23’ heel patch and a Jumpman logo embroidered on the lateral collar. A red webbing pull tab at the heel provides easy on and off. Orange and crimson accents reappear on the black foam midsole, featuring encapsulated Air-sole cushioning for a smooth ride.

name: Jordan 6 Retro Midnight Navy (2022) (GS)
story: The 2022 reissue of the Air Jordan 6 Retro GS ‘Midnight Navy’ brings back a 2000 colorway in big kid sizing. The build is faithful to the original, highlighted by a white leather upper with perforated detailing throughout the midfoot and padded collar. Navy accents appear on the molded tongue, spoiler-like heel tab, and the Jumpman branding hits that decorate the back heel and textile lace guard. The sneaker rests on a two-tone polyurethane midsole, fitted with an Air-sole unit in the heel and supported by a translucent rubber outsole.

name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Stage Haze
story: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG ‘Stage Haze’ features neutral tones on the foundational sneaker that started it all. The upper combines a white leather base with a grey suede heel overlay and a forefoot overlay in cracked black leather. Matching black accents settle on the signature Swoosh and a retro Wings logo stamped on the lateral ankle. Nike branding is outlined in Bleached Coral on the woven tongue tag, delivering a subtle flash of color. The high-top rests on a rubber cupsole that pairs white sidewalls with a grey rubber outsole.

name: Jordan 4 Retro Infrared
story: The Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘Infrared’ features distinctive color blocking that recalls the ‘Green Glow’ AJ4 release from 2013. The upper is crafted from smooth nubuck in a charcoal finish. A lighter shade of grey distinguishes the forefoot overlay, while black accents land on the quarter panel netting, structural wings and Jumpman-branded heel tab. The sneaker’s titular hue lights up the woven tongue tag and a quartet of molded eyelets. A polyurethane midsole packs visible Air-sole cushioning in the heel for a smooth ride.

name: Air Jordan 5 'Green Bean'
story: The 2022 edition of the Air Jordan 5 ‘Green Bean’ brings back a distinctive two-tone colorway initially released in 2006. Like the original, the mid-top carries a light grey nubuck upper entirely coated in a reflective finish. Bright green accents make their way to the interior lining and the embroidered Jumpman logo that decorate the heel and tongue. The vivid hue is repeated on the shark-tooth detailing that enlivens the dark grey polyurethane midsole. Underfoot, a translucent herringbone-tread rubber outsole provides grippy traction.

name: Union LA x Air Jordan 2 Retro SP 'Rattan'
story: The Union LA x Air Jordan 2 Retro SP ‘Rattan’ gives the iconic silhouette a comprehensive makeover, highlighted by a tan textile upper with tonal suede overlays. Perforated detailing on the quarter panel reveals an amber underlay, matching the sneaker’s molded eyelets and an attached ‘UN/LA’ tag. Additional branding elements include a woven Jumpman tag on the exposed foam tongue, along with an embossed Nike wordmark on the heel tab. A retro Wings logo decorates a woven tag affixed to the lateral collar. The sneaker is mounted on a cream-colored polyurethane midsole with encapsulated Air-sole cushioning.

name: Jordan 2 Retro Union Grey Fog
story: The Union LA x Air Jordan 2 Retro SP ‘Grey Fog’ delivers a modern take on the legacy silhouette originally released in 1986. Chris Gibbs and the Union crew dress the sneaker in a pale blue textile upper with tonal suede construction on the mudguard and quarter panel, featuring perforated detailing that reveals a bright blue underlay. The vibrant hue reappears on the sneaker’s molded eyelets, which is accented with a yellow ‘UN/LA’ tag on the lateral side. A woven tag looped over the collar displays a retro Wings logo, while an oversized Jumpman label adorns the exposed foam tongue. Anchoring the sneaker is a blue-tinged polyurethane midsole with encapsulated Air-sole cushioning.

name: Air Jordan 9 Retro 'Particle Grey'
story: The Air Jordan 9 Retro ‘Particle Grey’ delivers a neutral colorway of the ‘90s model that originally released during MJ’s first retirement from basketball. The retro silhouette is updated with a breathable black textile upper, secured with speed laces and accented with tonal stitch detailing. A nubuck mudguard in a neutral grey finish wraps around the heel and extends up the mid-cut collar. Contrasting hits of crimson land on the sneaker’s branding elements, including an Air Jordan tongue tag and a molded Jumpman emblem at the heel. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a matte grey polyurethane midsole with encapsulated Air-sole units in the forefoot and heel.

name: Jordan 13 Retro Del Sol
story: The Air Jordan 13 Retro ‘Del Sol’ combines sunny accents with OG-inspired color blocking and materials. The mid-top carries a white leather upper with dimpled overlays in matching white tumbled leather. A crimson Jumpman logo graces the tongue, while a green-tinged holographic cat eye adorns the lateral ankle. Yellow synthetic suede wraps the midfoot, heel, and lightweight Phylon midsole, fitted with Zoom Air cushioning in the forefoot and heel. Underfoot, the black panther-paw outsole features herringbone rubber pods and a carbon fiber shank plate.

name: Air Jordan 3 Retro SE 'Canvas'
story: The Air Jordan 3 Retro SE ‘Canvas’ updates Tinker Hatfield’s original 1988 design with a recrafted build. In lieu of traditional leather, the upper is constructed from Muslin canvas with forefoot and heel overlays in Cement Grey suede. University Red accents land on the sneaker’s lower eyelets, as well as Jumpman branding hits atop the tongue and molded heel panel. The sneaker rides on an off-white polyurethane midsole with visible Air-sole cushioning in the heel. Underfoot, a durable grey rubber outsole provides grippy traction.

name: adidas Stan Smith Southpark Stan Marsh
adidas Forum Low South Park AWESOM-O
Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Zen Master'
story: The Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘Zen Master’ features a unique design that pays tribute to Phil Jackson, the Chicago Bulls head coach who helmed the team’s six championship runs with Michael Jordan during the ‘90s. The classic silhouette makes use of a textile upper in a swirling mix of pink, purple and blue — a tie dye-like effect that nods to Jackson’s ‘Zen Master’ persona. A black woven tongue features Flight branding and a scarlet Jumpman icon, while a translucent TPU heel tab displays a raised Jumpman logo in black. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a polyurethane midsole with a visible Air-sole unit in the heel.

name: Nike Air Force 1 Low LX Off Noir Black
story: The Nike Air Force 1 Low LX ‘Off-Noir’ brings a minimalist, monochromatic aesthetic to the sneaker icon. The low-top carries a blacked-out nubuck upper with waxed laces, perforated detailing on the toe box, and a padded low-cut collar lined in breathable mesh. A white Swoosh is embroidered on the tongue tag and leather heel tab, the only elements that disrupt the shoe’s one-note finish. The retro silhouette rests on a Summit White rubber cupsole with encapsulated Air-sole cushioning in the heel.

name: Nike SB Dunk High Oski Great White
Blaze of Glory 'The Never Worn'
story: The PUMA Blaze of Glory ‘The Never Worn’ dresses the ‘90s runner with retro-aged materials, complete with visible glue stains and abrasions for an aged aesthetic. The sneaker features a black mesh upper with tonal suede overlays, grey perforated suede inserts and a glossy TPU cage integrated into the lacing system. Green zigzag stitching and a matching green heel tab deliver contrasting pops of color. A vintage pre-yellowed finish is applied to a lightweight EVA midsole with PUMA’s Trinomic cushioning technology.

name: Jordan 12 Retro Playoffs (2022)
story: The 2022 edition of the Air Jordan 12 Retro ‘Playoff’ brings back the shoe that Michael Jordan wore during his 1997 championship run. The mid-top sports an essential two-tone color scheme, featuring radiating stitched lines on the black leather upper and lizard-textured overlays in a contrasting white finish. The sneaker’s molded eyelets shine in metallic silver, while color-popped crimson accents land on the Jumpman-embroidered tongue and webbing heel loop. Performance benefits include full-length Zoom Air cushioning, a carbon fiber shank plate, and a rubber outsole with herringbone traction pods under the forefoot and heel.

name: Nike Dunk Low Essential Paisley Pack Green (W)
DC Comics x Cali Star Little Kid 'Wonder Woman'
DC Comics x Cali Star Jr 'Wonder Woman'
Jordan 6 Retro Mint Foam (W)
story: The women’s Air Jordan 6 Retro ‘Mint Foam’ adds pastel accents to the venerable silhouette that Michael Jordan wore when he clinched his first NBA championship. The upper pairs a light grey nubuck base with white leather overlays throughout the midfoot and heel. The latter is marked with an embroidered Jumpman icon in a soft mint green hue. Heritage details remain intact, including a molded tongue, spoiler-like heel tab, and Jumpman-branded lace guard. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a mint green polyurethane midsole, fitted with visible Air-sole cushioning and supported by a translucent rubber outsole.

name: Helly Hansen x Wild Rider 'Intense Blue'
adidas Yeezy Slide Onyx
story: The adidas Yeezy Slide ‘Onyx’ brings a stealthy monochrome finish to Kanye West’s futuristic sandal. A single piece of injected EVA foam is molded for a comfortable fit. The minimalist design is highlighted by ventilated open-toe construction and a soft footbed marked with debossed adidas branding. The serrated outsole features strategic groove placement, good for a combination of impact protection, exceptional grip, and improved impact protection.

name: Jordan 6 Retro UNC White
story: The Air Jordan 6 Retro ‘UNC Home’ features a familiar color combination that pays homage to MJ’s alma mater. The iconic silhouette carries a white leather upper with nubuck underlays in University Blue. Contrasting navy accents make their way to the molded TPU heel tab, textile collar lining and polyurethane midsole, the latter enhanced with visible Air-sole cushioning. Reflective perforations provide added visibility in low-light conditions, while a woven jock tag at the heel nods to the shoe’s varsity athletics theme.

name: Nike Hot Step Air Terra Drake NOCTA Black
Nike Hot Step Air Terra Drake NOCTA White
story: Crafted in partnership with Drake’s apparel brand, the NOCTA x Nike Hot Step Air Terra ‘White’ makes use of a tumbled leather upper in a blank-slate finish. A series of diagonal stitched lines, along with perforated detailing, embellish each of the sneaker’s side panels. Jeweled NOCTA branding is displayed atop the tongue, while chrome mini-Swooshes adorn the toe box and lateral heel. The sneaker rides on a matching white foam midsole, featuring sculpted sidewalls and an exposed yellow-tinged Air-sole unit under the heel.

adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Dazzling Blue
story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Dazzling Blue’ delivers a two-tone colorway of Kanye West’s popular lifestyle runner. The minimalist upper features flexible Primeknit construction, pitched to a solid black hue with contrasting threads woven throughout. A streak of royal blue cuts through the lateral side, complete with signature SPLY-350 branding. Responsive cushioning is provided by a full-length Boost midsole, entirely wrapped in a semi-translucent TPU cage for added durability.

name: New Balance 991 MiUK SNS Blue Yellow
New Balance 991 MiUK SNS Navy White
Nike Air Huarache WM Tortoise Shell (W)
Jordan 1 Mid Coconut Milk (W)
story: The women’s Air Jordan 1 Mid ‘Coconut Milk’ highlights neutral tones on a familiar silhouette modeled after the 1985 original. The leather upper combines a clean white base with cream-colored overlays and a black signature Swoosh. Additional branding elements include a woven Jumpman tongue tag and a retro Wings logo stamped on the lateral ankle. The mid-top rides on a traditional rubber cupsole, featuring encapsulated Air-sole cushioning under the heel.

name: Jordan 9 Retro Chile Red
story: The Air Jordan 9 Retro ‘Chile Red’ features a saturated design that recalls the ‘Motorboat Jones’ colorway from 2012. Stitched crimson textile is utilized on the upper, secured with a speed lacing system and bolstered with tonal patent leather along the mudguard, collar and heel. Contrasting black accents land on an Air Jordan tongue tag, molded eyelets and a prominent pull loop at the heel. The sneaker rides on a glossy red polyurethane midsole, enhanced with encapsulated Air-sole units in the forefoot and heel.
